@wangxinbot Thanks for the thorough review! All four issues have been addressed in the latest commit (caf16d5):

1. ✅ **Missing pmon pre-check** — Added `is_container_running(duthost, "pmon")` assertion before the grep
2. ✅ **Placeholder grep string** — Replaced `"test_string_placeholder"` with `"PMON_GREP_SAFE_TEST"` and added a comment explaining the string is intentionally a dummy (the panic is triggered by traversal, not by matching)
3. ✅ **Fragile dmesg baseline** — Switched from line-count indexing to timestamp-based `dmesg --since` filtering
4. ✅ **No delay before dmesg check** — Added `POST_GREP_SETTLE_SECS = 5` delay before post-grep dmesg capture

@ZhaohuiS PR description has been reformatted to match the `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md` template. Thanks for flagging!

@anamehra I tried it 3 times on our end and they all succeeded, I think this PR is good to merge, thanks!
